This paper deals with machine learning algorithms for classification of gene expression data sets. The paper specifically focuses on Transductive Support Vector Machines (TSVMs) and Recursive Feature Elimination (RFE) for feature selection. These topics are commonly studied in the machine learning subfields of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with gene expression data sets, which are often studied in the subfields of cs.CE (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper deals with classification, which is a common topic in the subfield of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, and cs.NE, in that order.
